  <scopecontent id="aspace_ae4eb36b838efba9c4afb103ffb62a2f">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence (1862-1872), legal papers (1861-1875), memorandum books (1870-1875), and account books of Wiley H. Scott and family of Ninevah and Unadilla, N.Y. pertaining to business ventures such as the "Scott House," a hotel in Ninevah N.Y. and the Scott Brewery in Unadilla, N.Y.</p>  </scopecontent>
